so it was fitting for billboard to create a chart in  dedicated to the thenrising genre birthed out of hiphop at the time mtv's influential yo mtv raps was only a few months old and acts like icet and nwa were not only ruling rap but beginning to enter the mainstream music conversation

while rap has evolved theres no denying its evergrowing power to celebrate the th anniversary of the billboards hot rap songs chart were counting down the top  songs in the tallys quartercentury history from saltnpepa to macklemore we've got the genre's past quartercentury covered
